===ACT===


==New installation:== 

1. Run the sql file database.sql:

$ mysql -p -u[user] < database.sql

2. In Apache; enable rewrite_module (/etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf) if it is not enabled yet:

LoadModule rewrite_module modules/mod_rewrite.so

3. Edit tracker_apache.conf, replacing 'tracker' with the actual installation directory in your web server's DocumentRoot

4. Copy the configuration file tracker_apache.conf to Apache's configuration dir (/etc/httpd/conf.d)

5. Get apache to reload its configuration:

$ service httpd reload

6. Edit [install_dir]/app/webroot/.htaccess and adjust the path on the RewriteBase command:

RewriteBase /tracker

7. Edit [install_dir]/app/webroot/index.php

Find this line:

define('CAKE_CORE_INCLUDE_PATH', DS . 'var' . DS . 'www' . DS . 'html' . DS . 'tracker');

And replace the name of the default installation directory, if needed.

8. Edit [install_dir]/app/config/database.php, and enter the correct database, username, and password.

